RHEL 9 server was used for remote server management using Cockpit

-> Install Cockpit
    dnf install cockpit -y

-> Enable service
    systemctl enable --now cockpit

-> Allow firewall access
   firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=cockpit
   firewall-cmd --reload

-> Cockpit runs on port:
   9090

-> Access URL
   https://172.16.100.15:9090

-> Why Cockpit?
Cockpit provides:
  -Web based Linux administration
  -Service monitoring
  -System resource monitoring
  -Storage and networking management

This allows GUI based management of Linux servers from browser.
